
[1]kindness

   KINDNESS, n. [from kind, the adjective.]

   1. Good will; benevolence; that temper or disposition which delights in
   contributing to the happiness of others, which is exercised cheerfully
   in gratifying their wishes, supplying their wants or alleviating their
   distresses; benignity of nature. Kindness ever accompanies love.

   There is no man whose kindness we may not sometime want, or by whose
   malice we may not sometime suffer.

   2. Act of good will; beneficence; any act of benevolence which promotes
   the happiness or welfare of others. Charity, hospitality, attentions to
   the wants of others, &c., are deemed acts of kindness, or kindnesses.
   Acts.28.
